Sure! Here's an example of how the irrigation management feature could be integrated with the existing code:
```javascript
// Define a function to retrieve crop water stress level and soil moisture status from drone data
function getIrrigationData() {
  // Use drone API to get current crop water stress level and soil moisture status
  const cropWaterStress = droneAPI.getCropWaterStress();
  const soilMoisture = droneAPI.getSoilMoisture();

  // Return the data as an object
  return {
    cropWaterStress,
    soilMoisture,
  };
}

// Define a function to create an optimized irrigation plan based on drone data
function createIrrigationPlan() {
  // Get the current crop and field data from the database
  const crop = db.getCurrentCrop();
  const field = db.getCurrentField();

  // Get the current weather data from a weather API
  const weather = weatherAPI.getCurrentWeather();

  // Get the irrigation data from the drone
  const irrigationData = getIrrigationData();

  // Use the data to create an optimized irrigation plan
  const plan = irrigationAlgorithm.createPlan(crop, field, weather, irrigationData);

  // Store the plan in the database
  db.saveIrrigationPlan(plan);

  // Return the plan
  return plan;
}

// Define a function to update the irrigation plan in real-time based on drone data
function updateIrrigationPlan() {
  // Get the current irrigation plan from the database
  const plan = db.getCurrentIrrigationPlan();

  // Get the current irrigation data from the drone
  const irrigationData = getIrrigationData();

  // Update the plan based on the new data
  const updatedPlan = irrigationAlgorithm.updatePlan(plan, irrigationData);

  // Store the updated plan in the database
  db.saveIrrigationPlan(updatedPlan);

  // Return the updated plan
  return updatedPlan;
}
```
This code defines three functions related to irrigation management:

1. `getIrrigationData()`: This function retrieves the current crop water stress level and soil moisture status from the drone API.
2. `createIrrigationPlan()`: This function creates an optimized irrigation plan based on the current crop and field data, current weather data from a weather API, and the current irrigation data from the drone.
3. `updateIrrigationPlan()`: This function updates the current irrigation plan in real-time based on the current irrigation data from the drone.

These functions can be integrated into the existing farm management app code to provide real-time irrigation management functionality based on drone data.
